---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About Renato" description="Meet Renato Molina Toth — the software engineer and nutritionist behind PKD Cure Tracker.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <nav class="mb-8">
      <a href="/about" class="text-sm text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 inline-flex items-center gap-1">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
        </svg>
        About
      </a>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Meet the person behind this project</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-6 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
      <p class="text-lg">
        Hi 👋 I'm <a href="http://renatomolina.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-bold text-gray-900 hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">Renato Molina Toth</a> — a software engineer and nutritionist based in Canada.
      </p>

      <p>
        PKD runs in my family. I've been involved with the PKD community for years, following the research, connecting with other patients and caregivers, and trying to make sense of a rapidly evolving landscape of treatments and clinical trials.
      </p>

      <p>
        I built PKD Cure Tracker because I saw a gap: the information is out there — in journal papers, on ClinicalTrials.gov, in conference abstracts, in Facebook groups — but it's fragmented and hard to keep up with. As someone with both a technical background and training in nutrition, I wanted to create a single place where our community can find clear, impartial, and up-to-date information without wading through noise.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-xl p-6 mt-8">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
          Have a suggestion, correction, or want to collaborate? Reach out — this project is built for the community, and community input makes it better.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
